channel.title: Need help with nulled vbulletin!
channel.description: Hey guys, does anyone know the whole concept of setting up a Nulled Vbulletin? I can't find a tutorial anywhere.. i tried google and everything... Please don't flame me, I am new to this :|. Please help me! x.x Post a tutorial or something to help me, maybe even send me a private message and I can get teamviewer assistance. Thanks for who ever helps me!

item.title: Need help with nulled vbulletin!
item.dc:creator: @Ix_Soulcist_xI Soulcist
item.description:
@Ix_Soulcist_xI wrote:

[quote=“T4_, post:9, topic:399448”][quote author=drubrkletern link=topic=496580.msg3631780#msg3631780 date=1308280171]
wth does it cost that much? What makes it special?
[/quote]
You get unlimited upgrades as long as your license is valid, and if your upgrades expire, you can install the last update you were on whilst valid anytime for the rest of your life. vBulletin also has REALLY good support with a response time of < 30min for all tickets. vBulletin is also VERY stable and has numerous mods/extra features that are FREE.[/quote]
This would be true, never had a problem with customer support and had a lot of fast responses.

Mybb, SMF, vBulletin (paid) etc etc are all great, using nulled is plain stupid.
